item.title: Anastasia add a quote by Borges
item.description: "Once I am dead, there will be no lack of pious hands to throw me over the railing; my grave will be the fathomless air; my body will sink endlessly and decay and dissolve in the wind generated by the fall, which is infinite." -- Borges

item.title: Anastasia add a quote by Osip Mandelstam
item.description: "And I walk out of space Into an overgrown garden of values, And tear up seeming stability And self-comprehension of causes. And your, infinity, textbook I read by myself, without people - Leafless, savage medical book, A problem book of gigantic radicals." -- Osip Mandelstam
